  "number": 1085,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1085",
  "title": "Should we use lodash?",
  "body": "PROS:\n- no brainer, use a single library for all data manipulation/check\n- widely used\n- no need to learn most JavaScript data manipulation/check methods\n\nCONS:\n- heavy from a library POV. Lodash is 10% of our minified build\n- no need to learn most JavaScript data manipulation/check methods\n\nContext:\n- we can use ES6 **syntax** for arrow functions\n- our browser support starts at ES5, which means we can access Array.map, filter, forEach\n- we may have missing helper methods/options solved by using lodash methods (like https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/427521e9d82a23315e3ad7cf318313f265f3815c/src/widgets/numeric-selector/numeric-selector.js#L85-L86)\n- we have to chose between lodash 3, lodash 4 and ultimately this duplicate code with our users (see #984)\n- we could go with the facebook approach and share and create only what we really need: https://github.com/facebook/fbjs\n- we do not know the performance implications of using lodash\n\nFrom our current lodash usage in instantsearch.js (search \"lodash/\"), the only \"tricky\" non ES5, non arrow function solvable use case of lodash seems to be lodash/find (Array.find).\n",
